caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="lunch pouring 2" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/lunch-pouring-2.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/lunch-pouring-2.jpg?w=720" /></a>\n<a href=''https://en.blog.wordpress.com/2015/11/27/field-notes-wine-tourism-conference-2015/wp-bags-at-expo/''><img width="150" height="150" src="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/wp-bags-at-expo.jpg?w=150&#038;h=150" class="attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail" alt="WordPress.com and wine" data-attachment-id="33528" data-orig-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/wp-bags-at-expo.jpg" data-orig-size="2448,2448" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;2.4&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;iPhone 5c&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1447869862&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;4.12&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;320&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.05&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="WP bags at Expo" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/wp-bags-at-expo.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/wp-bags-at-expo.jpg?w=720" /></a>\n<a href=''https://en.blog.wordpress.com/2015/11/27/field-notes-wine-tourism-conference-2015/marjorie-wordpress-wtc15-expo/''><img width="150" height="150" src="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/marjorie-wordpress-wtc15-expo.jpg?w=150&#038;h=150" class="attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail" alt="Marjorie and WordPress.com at Expo" data-attachment-id="33527" data-orig-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/marjorie-wordpress-wtc15-expo.jpg" data-orig-size="1746,1746" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;2.4&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;iPhone 5c&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1447862440&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;4.12&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;160&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.05&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Marjorie WordPress WTC15 Expo" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/marjorie-wordpress-wtc15-expo.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/marjorie-wordpress-wtc15-expo.jpg?w=720" /></a>\n<a href=''https://en.blog.wordpress.com/2015/11/27/field-notes-wine-tourism-conference-2015/marjorie-presenting/''><img width="150" height="150" src="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/marjorie-presenting.jpg?w=150&#038;h=150" class="attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail" alt="Designing Websites with Marjorie Asturias" data-attachment-id="33529" data-orig-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/marjorie-presenting.jpg" data-orig-size="2209,2209" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;2.4&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;iPhone 5c&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1448013589&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;4.12&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;80&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.05&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Designing Websites for 2016 and Beyond at Wine Tourism Conference" data-image-description="&lt;p&gt;WordPress.com Designing Websites for 2016 and Beyond at Wine Tourism Conference 2015&lt;/p&gt;\n" data-medium-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/marjorie-presenting.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/marjorie-presenting.jpg?w=720" /></a>\n<br />\nThis passion is perfect for blogging. Everything has a story in wine tourism: the architecture of the tasting room, the land, the family, the wine. These are small businesses that feed naturally into the Go Local movement, in which customers want to meet the people who are growing and making local food and wine.</p>\n<p>Wine tour guides and emerging wineries are small businesses. They have minimal advertising budgets, but they have fascinating stories to tell. Websites, blogs, and social networking are powerful, inexpensive tools for connecting with their customers and getting the word out about the wine and land they love so much.</p>\n<div class="embed-mesh">\n<div style="width: 100%; position: relative; max-width: 720px" class="mesh-embed">\n<div style="padding-top: 100%"></div>\n<p><iframe src="https://me.sh/14aefik?oembed=720" style="position: absolute; top: 0; min-width: 200px; min-height: 200px; height: 100%" width="100%" height="500px" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div>\n</div>\n<p>Vintners poured wine and shared their stories and passion with us, and Marjorie and I were thrilled to return the favor. We talked about blogging as a guerrilla marketing tool, stressed the importance of having a website and an online presence, and even helped a local wine concierge, <a href="http://vino301.com/">Vino 301,</a> ensure her site is mobile ready. In addition, Marjorie presented a much-appreciated session on <a href="http://marjorieasturias.com/2015/11/20/wine-tourism-conference-presentation/">Designing Websites for 2016 and beyond</a>, and I succumbed to the <a href="http://andreabadgley.com/2015/11/20/tasting-wine-in-loudoun-county-virginia/">beauty of the region</a>, taking notes for when my husband and I one day get away to explore the wineries of Virginia.</p><br />Filed under: <a href=''https://en.blog.wordpress.com/category/events/''>Events</a>  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/en.blog.wordpress.com/33500/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/en.blog.wordpress.com/33500/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="https://pixel.wp.com/b.gif?host=en.blog.wordpress.com&#038;blog=3584907&#038;post=33500&#038;subd=en.blog&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1" width="1" height="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:87:"https://en.blog.wordpress.com/2015/11/27/field-notes-wine-tourism-conference-2015/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"12";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:2:{s:9:"thumbnail";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:3:"url";s:72:"http://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/stone-tower-wine-14.jpg?w=150";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"content";a:8:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:7:"\n			\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:2:{s:3:"url";s:72:"http://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/stone-tower-wine-14.jpg?w=150";s:6:"medium";s:5:"image";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:29:"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/";a:1:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:54:"Wine and WordPress.com at Wine Tourism Conference 2015";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:4:"type";s:4:"html";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:7:"\n	