(9, 1, '2015-08-20 03:09:31', '2015-08-20 03:09:31', '[pjc_slideshow slide_type="blog-slideshot"]The years from 1969 to present saw networked devices balloon from <a href="http://www.walthowe.com/navnet/history.html">four university computers</a> connected via the ARPANET to about two billion humans frequently accessing the Internet today. In the near future that number will exponentially multiply again, from a couple billion networked devices to <a href="http://www.gartner.com/newsroom/id/2684616"><em>tens of billions</em> of embedded processors</a>. Every aspect of our lives will be connected by networked devices: homes, workplaces, vehicles, appliances, tools, toys --you name it.', 'Java: The once and future king of Internet programming', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'java-the-once-and-future-king-of-internet-programming', '', '', '2015-08-21 16:58:12', '2015-08-21 16:58:12', '', 0, 'http://localhost/InnoculateIT/?p=9', 0, 'post', '', 0),
